<TITLE> Thick fog disrupts ferry services across Padma </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Madaripur, Jan 3 (bdnews24.com)  Ferry services remained suspended on Paturia-Daulatdia and Mawa-Kawrakandhi routes on Sunday due to poor visibility caused by dense fog. bdnews24.com Manikganj correspondent reported ferries resumed operation on Paturia-Daulatdia route at 9am after the services were stopped for three hours. Bangladesh Inland Water Transport Corporation (BIWTC) officials said hundreds of vehicles were stranded on both piers of the route during that period. Ashraf Ullah, manager of BIWTC Aricha office, said there was a huge traffic snarls on the Dhaka-Aricha highway. Reports from Madaripur said dense fog disrupted ferry services for three-and-a-half hours on Mawa-Kawrakandi route. BIWTC official Abu Alam Hawlader said six ferries remained stranded on the Padma river since 7am as they could not move due to thick fog. bdn
